ormally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isabel Scobhull was born about 1404, in East Harptree, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, her father, Robert Scobhull, was 46 and her mother, Eleanor, was 41. She married Thomas Cheddar about 1420, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1404–":"umbes 1404–Surnud","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1380–1443":"1380–1443","1421–1443":"1421–1443","1425–1464":"1425–1464","1451–1498":"1451–1498","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1451":"1451","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1404":"umbes 1404","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1421":"1421","1498":"1498","1443":"1443","1365":"1365","1464":"1464","about 1425":"umbes 1425","about 1420":"umbes 1420","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","East Harptree, Somerset, England":"East Harptree, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1404–":"noin 1404–Kuollut","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1380–1443":"1380–1443","1421–1443":"1421–1443","1425–1464":"1425–1464","1451–1498":"1451–1498","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1451":"1451","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1404":"noin 1404","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1421":"1421","1498":"1498","1443":"1443","1365":"1365","1464":"1464","about 1425":"noin 1425","about 1420":"noin 1420","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","East Harptree, Somerset, England":"East Harptree, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1404–":"environ 1404–Décédée","1404–Female":"1404–Décédée","1380–1443":"1380–1443","1421–1443":"1421–1443","1425–1464":"1425–1464","1451–149